                   and locations of sampled isolates can be used to
                   reconstruct the spatiotemporal dynamics of pathogens
                   during outbreaks. Thus far, phylogenetic methods have
                   been used to tackle this issue. Although these
                   approaches have proved useful for informing on the
                   spread of pathogens, they do not aim at directly
