                   interval = 3.13, 4.30), similar to that from the
                   Poisson approach but with a better model fit. Our
                   approach further estimated kt {$<$}0.5 at the start
                   of both waves, indicating appreciable heterogeneity
                   in transmission. We also found that kt decreased
                   sharply to around 0.4 when a large cluster of
                   infections occurred. Conclusions: Our proposed
                   approach can contribute to the estimation of Rt and
                   monitoring of the time-varying dispersion parameters
